fields.short_description: Our flagship sparkling wine. Known for its classic, crisp style with rich complexity and a fine mousse.
fields.name: Gruet

fields.description: Cabernet Sauvignon is the noblest of grape varieties and Guenoc California Cabernet shows “respect” by putting the fruit front and center.  Classic red and black cherry are surrounded by cushiony tannins.  The coronation is a whisper of vanilla oak on the finish… all hail king Cab!
fields.name: Guenoc Cabernet

fields.description:
Versatility has made Chardonnay the undisputed heavyweight champion of California white wines. Guenoc Chardonnay is crafted to find the balance between acidity and richness. Enjoy the harmony of ripe tropical fruit, vanilla oak and citrus peel… ABC’ers look out!

ABC’ers stands for “Anything But Chardonnay” and because of the availability of the varietal, there are some who feel Chardonnay is just too boring.  Nothing could be further from the truth.  Good Chardonnay is a thing of beauty and very difficult to achieve.  It takes winemaking skill to get the most fruit possible while accompanying it with a touch of barrel influenced, ML induced wine.  We hope you appreciate the effort!
fields.name: Guenoc Chardonnay

fields.description: Bullied and accused, the only crime Merlot has committed is that of luxury.  The suppleness of Merlot can not be denied, this Guenoc California Merlot offers ample textured tannins to drape the cherry and dark chocolate flavor… Merlot is back!  Since the 2004 release of the movie “Sideways” Merlot sales have suffered.  For the savvy oenophile the result has been almost a decade of great value.  Merlot, at its finest, is perhaps the best of the Bordeaux grapes.  The Guenoc California Selection Merlot continues this value stream and rewards those who break from the herd.
fields.name: Guenoc Merlot

fields.description:
Like many old world traditions in America, Guenoc California Pinot Grigio takes this popular white variety of Italy and gives it a California style all its own.  Instead of “bone dry” this floral, aromatic wine finishes sweet-tart and brings flavors of honeydew melon and lemon grass… prego!

Blended with a touch of Moscatto to enhance the fruit and bring out a touch of sweetness, the Guenoc California Selection Pinot Grigio is a true California original.
fields.name: Guenoc Pinot Grigio

fields.description:
The tropical flavors created by California sunshine separate Guenoc Sauvignon Blanc from the rest of the world.  Leaving the grassy characters “down under” we craft our Sauvignon Blanc to enhance the mouthwatering flavors of grapefruit, pineapple and mango… don’t forget your sunscreen!

The protected in-land valleys of California get plenty of sunshine and the Guenoc Valley is no exception.  Every day during the growing season, temperatures fluctuate nearly 50 degrees from a peak of nearly 100°F down to 50°F at night.  The warm temperatures ripen the fruit and allow the pyrazines (the cut grass, green pepper or jalapeño flavors) to change into tropical notes, while the diurnal low temps keep the acidity bright.  Warm climate SB has all the pineapple, guava and mango of a fruit smoothie!
fields.name: Guenoc Sauvignon Blanc

fields.short_description: Bold fruit aromas and flavors centered on red plum and boysenberry, and a rich and mouthfilling texture with soft tannins.
fields.description: The 2010 vintage started with a cool and fairly wet spring that remained mostly frost free. The late rains generated a healthy canopy, but one that required careful management to avoid green flavors. The cool spring evolved into an exceptionally cool summer, punctuated by a three-day heat spike in August which reduced yields in many varieties. September and October, however, were warm, giving us the ripeness we were waiting for, and we harvested the last of our Cabernet on October 27th.
fields.name: Rodney Strong Cabernet

fields.short_description: Creamy and crisp, with abundant fruit character, mineral and toasty oak flavors.
fields.description: The 2011 vintage started off cool and damp, with little to no frost.  late rains continued until July, with almost two inches of rain in the month of June. The end of the rainy season led to a cool weather pattern for most of the summer, With average high temperatures around 80 degrees for both July and August. The heat finally returned in  September, with one six day stretch of temperatures in the 90s, exactly what the vintage needed, and we harvested the last of our Chalk Hill Chardonnay on September 27th under ideal conditions.
fields.name: Rodney Strong Chardonnay

fields.short_description: Soft and silky, with intriguing floral and crushed pomegranate aromas, this medium bodied wine was aged for nine months in small, French oak barrels which added a hint of toasty vanilla and spice complexity.
fields.description: Rod Strong was among the first modern wine pioneers with a vision to plant Pinot Noir in the Russian River Valley. in 1968, he planted our heritage River East Vineyard in the alluvial clay-loam soils adjacent to the winery in Healdsburg. Today the Russian River Valley is well established as one of the premier Pinot Noir growing regions in the world and we continue to rely on the original River East Vineyard as a core contributor to our estate vineyard bottling.
fields.name: Rodney Strong Pinot Noir
